Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeblendspace2d.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for configuring an AnimationNodeBlendSpace2D.

Properties:
*   auto_triangles (bool): If true, the blend space will automatically triangulate the points. Default: true.
*   blend_mode (BlendMode): Controls how the blend space mixes animations. Default: 0.
*   max_space (Vector2): The blend space's maximum X and Y coordinates. Default: Vector2(1, 1).
*   min_space (Vector2): The blend space's minimum X and Y coordinates. Default: Vector2(-1, -1).
*   snap (Vector2): The blend space's snap value for X and Y coordinates. Default: Vector2(0.1, 0.1).
*   sync (bool): If true, the blend space will synchronize its playback with other blend spaces. Default: false.
*   x_label (String): The label for the X axis of the blend space. Default: "x".
*   y_label (String): The label for the Y axis of the blend space. Default: "y".
