Document: AnimationNodeBlendSpace2D
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeblendspace2d.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for configuring an AnimationNodeBlendSpace2D, including blend behavior, axis limits, and labels.

Property Descriptions:
* auto_triangles (bool): If true, the blend space is triangulated automatically. The mesh updates every time you add or remove points with add_blend_point() and remove_blend_point(). Default: true
* blend_mode (BlendMode): Controls the interpolation between animations. Default: 0
* max_space (Vector2): The blend space's X and Y axes' upper limit for the points' position. See add_blend_point(). Default: Vector2(1, 1)
* min_space (Vector2): The blend space's X and Y axes' lower limit for the points' position. See add_blend_point(). Default: Vector2(-1, -1)
* snap (Vector2): Position increment to snap to when moving a point. Default: Vector2(0.1, 0.1)
* sync (bool): If false, the blended animations' frame are stopped when the blend value is 0. If true, forcing the blended animations to advance frame. Default: false
* x_label (String): Name of the blend space's X axis. Default: "x"
* y_label (String): Name of the blend space's Y axis. Default: "y"
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimationNodeBlendSpace2D
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeblendspace2d.rst
Summary: This section describes methods for managing blend points and triangles within an AnimationNodeBlendSpace2D, including adding, removing, reordering, and querying their properties.

Method: add_blend_point(node: AnimationRootNode, pos: Vector2, at_index: int = -1, name: StringName = &"")
Adds a new point with `name` that represents a `node` at the position set by `pos`. You can insert it at a specific index using the `at_index` argument. If you use the default value for `at_index`, the point is inserted at the end of the blend points array. Note: If no name is provided, safe index is used as reference. In the future, empty names will be deprecated, so explicitly passing a name is recommended.

Method: add_triangle(x: int, y: int, z: int, at_index: int = -1)
Creates a new triangle using three points `x`, `y`, and `z`. Triangles can overlap. You can insert the triangle at a specific index using the `at_index` argument. If you use the default value for `at_index`, the point is inserted at the end of the blend points array.

Method: find_blend_point_by_name(name: StringName) -> int
Returns the index of the blend point with the given `name`. Returns `-1` if no blend point with that name is found.

Method: get_blend_point_count() -> int
Returns the number of points in the blend space.

Method: get_blend_point_name(point: int) -> StringName
Returns the name of the blend point at index `point`.

Method: get_blend_point_node(point: int) -> AnimationRootNode
Returns the AnimationRootNode referenced by the point at index `point`.

Method: get_blend_point_position(point: int) -> Vector2
Returns the position of the point at index `point`.

Method: get_triangle_count() -> int
Returns the number of triangles in the blend space.

Method: get_triangle_point(triangle: int, point: int) -> int
Returns the position of the point at index `point` in the triangle of index `triangle`.

Method: remove_blend_point(point: int) -> void
Removes the point at index `point` from the blend space.

Method: remove_triangle(triangle: int) -> void
Removes the triangle at index `triangle` from the blend space.

Method: reorder_blend_point(from_index: int, to_index: int) -> void
Swaps the blend points at indices `from_index` and `to_index`, exchanging their positions and properties.

Method: set_blend_point_name(point: int, name: StringName) -> void
Sets the name of the blend point at index `point`. If the name conflicts with an existing point, a unique name will be generated automatically.

Method: set_blend_point_node(point: int, node: AnimationRootNode) -> void
Changes the AnimationNode referenced by the point at index `point`.

Method: set_blend_point_position(point: int, pos: Vector2) -> void
Updates the position of the point at index `point` in the blend space.